08/12/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer has formally invited representatives of Bosnia and Herzegovina, Montenegro and Serbia to sign the agreement on their accession to NATO's Partnership for Peace Programme on Thursday (December 14th) in Brussels. 
The decision to admit the three countries was made at the NATO summit in Riga last week. 
(RTRS, PBS, Fena, Tanjug, Beta, B92, Mina - 07/12/06)
